WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:03.394
In every generation
there is a chosen one.

00:03.438 --> 00:06.049
She alone will stand
against the vampires,

00:06.092 --> 00:08.833
the demons
and the forces of darkness.

00:08.878 --> 00:10.880
She is the slayer.

00:23.457 --> 00:26.460
♪

00:50.484 --> 00:53.487
♪

01:09.504 --> 01:11.897
Are you sure
this is a good idea?

01:11.941 --> 01:14.161
It's a great idea.
Now come on.

01:20.906 --> 01:22.820
Do you go to school here?

01:22.864 --> 01:24.388
I used to.

01:24.432 --> 01:26.912
On top of the gym,
it's so cool.

01:26.956 --> 01:28.652
You can see
the whole town.

01:31.003 --> 01:34.354
I-I-I-I don't want
to go up there.

01:34.397 --> 01:36.400
Oh, you can't wait, huh?

01:36.444 --> 01:38.706
We're just gonna
get in trouble.

01:40.448 --> 01:45.843
Yeah, you can count
on it.

01:45.888 --> 01:47.150
[gasps]

01:47.194 --> 01:48.673
What was that?

01:48.716 --> 01:50.152
What was what?

01:50.197 --> 01:51.849
I heard a noise.

01:51.894 --> 01:53.417
It's nothing.

01:53.460 --> 01:56.420
Well, uh, maybe
it's something.

01:56.463 --> 01:58.901
Well, maybe
it's some thing.

01:58.944 --> 02:00.728
That's not funny.

02:03.340 --> 02:06.126
Hello.

02:08.954 --> 02:12.828
There's nobody here.

02:12.871 --> 02:14.307
Are you sure?

02:14.350 --> 02:16.658
Yes, I'm sure.

02:18.354 --> 02:21.444
Okay.

02:21.489 --> 02:23.012
[snarling]

02:23.055 --> 02:24.318
Aah! Aah!

02:30.105 --> 02:33.195
[wolf howling]

02:33.240 --> 02:35.284
♪

03:24.028 --> 03:27.032
♪

03:57.324 --> 03:59.629
♪

04:10.118 --> 04:12.774
WOMAN:
Buffy!

04:12.817 --> 04:14.862
I'm up, Mom.

04:14.906 --> 04:17.692
MOM: Don't want to be late
for your first day!

04:17.735 --> 04:19.737
No...

04:19.781 --> 04:22.130
wouldn't want that.

04:22.173 --> 04:25.089
♪ Hey, man, I'm talking to you

04:25.134 --> 04:27.918
♪ What are you singing
and what is true? ♪

04:27.963 --> 04:32.880
♪ Keep your beliefs
away from me ♪

04:32.923 --> 04:35.404
♪ Hey, man, listen
when I'm talking to you... ♪

04:39.235 --> 04:41.281
Okay.

04:41.324 --> 04:42.803
[sighs]

04:42.846 --> 04:44.935
Have a good time.

04:44.980 --> 04:46.547
I know you're gonna
make friends right away.

04:46.590 --> 04:47.808
Just think positive.

04:50.463 --> 04:51.942
And, honey...

04:53.336 --> 04:55.468
Try not to get kicked out.

04:55.512 --> 04:57.252
I promise.

04:57.297 --> 04:58.384
Okay.

04:58.427 --> 04:59.386
♪ We are the antiheroes

04:59.428 --> 05:02.302
♪ Living in society

05:02.345 --> 05:05.870
♪ Antiheroes...

05:05.913 --> 05:08.394
Excuse me. Coming through.
Pardon me.

05:08.437 --> 05:09.396
Watch it.Excuse me.

05:09.439 --> 05:10.571
Whoa!
Aah!
Whoa!

05:10.613 --> 05:12.355
Excuse me. Can't stop.

05:12.399 --> 05:15.052
Please move. Whoa!
Excuse me.

05:15.096 --> 05:16.793
Whoa.

05:19.622 --> 05:23.452
Oh, God!
I'm okay. I feel good.

05:23.497 --> 05:25.454
Willow! You're so very much
the person

05:25.499 --> 05:27.456
that I wanted to see.

05:27.500 --> 05:29.024
Oh, really?

05:29.067 --> 05:31.331
Yeah. You know, I kind of had
a problem with the math.

05:31.374 --> 05:32.941
Uh, which part?

05:32.983 --> 05:34.115
The math.

05:34.158 --> 05:35.596
Can you help me out
tonight, please?

05:35.639 --> 05:36.858
Be my study buddy?

05:36.901 --> 05:38.338
Well, what's in it
for me?

05:38.380 --> 05:39.817
A shiny nickel.

05:39.860 --> 05:42.079
Okay. Do you have
Theories in Trig?

05:42.124 --> 05:43.386
You should
check it out.

05:43.430 --> 05:44.822
"Check it out"?

05:44.865 --> 05:47.042
From the library--
where the books live.

05:47.084 --> 05:48.564
Right. I'm there.

05:48.608 --> 05:49.566
See? I want to change.

05:49.610 --> 05:50.653
Hey, hey!

05:50.697 --> 05:52.090
Hey, Jesse. What's what?

05:52.134 --> 05:53.264
New girl.

05:53.308 --> 05:54.528
That's right. I saw her.

05:54.571 --> 05:55.920
Pretty much a hottie.

05:55.963 --> 05:57.399
I heard someone
was transferring.

05:57.444 --> 05:58.401
So tell.

05:58.444 --> 06:00.055
Tell what?

06:00.098 --> 06:01.882
What's the sitch?
What do you know about her?

06:01.925 --> 06:03.754
New girl.

06:03.798 --> 06:06.235
Well, you're certainly
a font of nothing.

06:06.278 --> 06:08.062
Buffy Summers.

06:08.105 --> 06:11.413
Sophomore, late of Hemery High
in Los Angeles.

06:11.458 --> 06:13.329
Interesting record.

06:13.372 --> 06:15.983
Quite a career.

06:21.423 --> 06:23.730
Welcome to Sunnydale.

06:23.774 --> 06:26.386
A clean slate, Buffy,
that's what you get here.

06:26.428 --> 06:28.605
What's past is past.

06:28.649 --> 06:31.259
We're not interested in what
it says on a piece of paper,

06:31.302 --> 06:32.696
even if it says...

06:33.827 --> 06:36.264
Whoa.

06:36.307 --> 06:37.439
Mr. Flutie...

06:37.483 --> 06:38.875
All the kids here
are free to call me Bob.

06:38.920 --> 06:39.747
Bob...

06:39.790 --> 06:41.052
But they don't.

06:41.096 --> 06:43.271
I know my transcripts
are a little...

06:43.314 --> 06:44.490
colorful.

06:44.533 --> 06:46.927
Hey, we're not caring
about that.

06:46.971 --> 06:49.408
Do you think,
uh, "colorful"

06:49.451 --> 06:51.062
is the word?

06:51.105 --> 06:53.021
Not, uh, dismal?

06:53.064 --> 06:54.413
Wasn't that bad.

06:54.456 --> 06:55.805
You burned down the gym.

06:55.850 --> 06:56.807
[sighs] I did.

06:56.850 --> 06:58.678
I really did, but...

06:58.721 --> 07:00.680
but you're not seeing
the big picture here.

07:00.723 --> 07:02.509
I mean, that gym
was full of vampi...

07:03.771 --> 07:05.728
Uh, asbestos.

07:05.773 --> 07:07.122
Buffy, don't worry.

07:07.165 --> 07:09.166
Any other school...

07:09.211 --> 07:11.300
they might say,
"Watch your step"

07:11.343 --> 07:13.737
or "We'll be
watching you,"

07:13.781 --> 07:16.697
but that's just
not the way here.

07:16.740 --> 07:20.048
We want to service
your needs

07:20.091 --> 07:22.572
and help you
to respect our needs.

07:22.615 --> 07:25.966
And if your needs
and our needs don't mesh...

07:32.146 --> 07:34.497
[indistinct conversations]

07:37.500 --> 07:39.632
Ooh! Oh, sorry.

07:39.675 --> 07:40.721
That's okay.

07:40.764 --> 07:42.418
Oh.

07:43.723 --> 07:45.552
Can I have you?

07:47.379 --> 07:49.512
Uh, [chuckles]
can I helpyou?

07:49.555 --> 07:50.512
Uh, thanks.

07:50.557 --> 07:53.384
I don't know you, do I?

07:53.428 --> 07:54.648
I'm Buffy.

07:54.691 --> 07:55.562
I'm new.

07:55.605 --> 07:57.432
Xander is-is me.

07:57.476 --> 07:59.043
Hi.

07:59.086 --> 08:00.480
Oh, thanks.

08:00.523 --> 08:01.742
Well, uh,

08:01.785 --> 08:03.526
maybe I'll see you
around.

08:03.569 --> 08:05.048
Maybe at school...

08:05.093 --> 08:07.487
since we both...

08:07.529 --> 08:08.966
go there.

08:09.009 --> 08:10.533
Great.

08:10.576 --> 08:12.492
It was nice to meet you.

08:16.016 --> 08:17.932
We both go to school.

08:17.975 --> 08:18.932
Very suave.

08:18.975 --> 08:20.891
Very not pathetic.

08:20.935 --> 08:22.457
Oh. Hey!

08:22.502 --> 08:24.634
Hey! You forgot your...

08:25.766 --> 08:27.158
stake.

08:33.600 --> 08:36.558
It's estimated
that about 25 million people

08:36.602 --> 08:39.039
died in that one four-year span.

08:39.082 --> 08:41.563
But the fun part
of the black plague

08:41.607 --> 08:43.826
is that it originated
in Europe how?

08:45.611 --> 08:50.529
As an early form
of germ warfare.

08:50.572 --> 08:52.488
If you'll look
at the map on page 63,

08:52.532 --> 08:55.056
you can trace
the spread of the disease

08:55.099 --> 08:57.448
into Rome and then north...

08:57.493 --> 08:58.450
Thanks.

08:58.494 --> 08:59.538
Sure.

08:59.581 --> 09:01.278
And this popular plague

09:01.322 --> 09:02.889
led to what social changes?

09:02.932 --> 09:04.065
Steve?

09:04.107 --> 09:05.806
[bell rings]

09:08.677 --> 09:10.461
Hi, I'm Cordelia.

09:10.505 --> 09:11.985
I'm Buffy.

09:12.028 --> 09:14.553
If you're looking for
a textbook of your very own,

09:14.596 --> 09:16.424
there's probably a few
in the library.

09:16.467 --> 09:18.470
Oh, great. Thanks.
Where would that be?

09:18.514 --> 09:20.559
I'll show you. Come on.

09:20.602 --> 09:22.386
So you're from Hemery,
right? In L.A.?

09:22.431 --> 09:23.562
Yeah.

09:23.605 --> 09:25.520
Oh, I would kill
to live in L.A.--

09:25.565 --> 09:27.304
that close
to that many shoes.

09:29.480 --> 09:31.352
Well, you'll be okay here.

09:31.395 --> 09:32.788
If you hang with me
and mine,

09:32.832 --> 09:34.573
you'll be accepted
in no time.

09:34.616 --> 09:38.099
Of course, we do have to test
your coolness factor.

09:38.142 --> 09:40.448
You're from L.A.,
so you can skip the written,

09:40.491 --> 09:41.971
but let's see.

09:42.015 --> 09:43.451
Vamp nail polish?

09:43.495 --> 09:45.453
Um, over?

09:45.496 --> 09:46.933
Soover.

09:46.976 --> 09:48.543
James Spader?

09:48.587 --> 09:50.459
He needs to call me.

09:50.501 --> 09:51.981
Frappuccinos?

09:52.025 --> 09:53.461
Trendy but tasty.

09:53.504 --> 09:54.462
John Tesh.

09:54.505 --> 09:55.551
The devil.

09:55.595 --> 09:57.073
That was pretty much
a gimme,

09:57.118 --> 09:58.379
but you passed.

09:58.423 --> 09:59.947
Oh, good.

09:59.990 --> 10:01.251
Willow.

10:01.296 --> 10:02.775
Nice dress.

10:02.818 --> 10:06.735
Good to know you've seen
the softer side of Sears.

10:06.779 --> 10:09.565
Uh, well-well,
my mom picked it out.

10:09.609 --> 10:11.261
No wonder you're such
a guy magnet.

10:11.306 --> 10:12.524
Are you done?

10:13.917 --> 10:15.788
Oh!

10:17.006 --> 10:18.442
If you want
to fit in here,

10:18.486 --> 10:21.707
the first rule is:
know your losers.

10:21.750 --> 10:23.840
Once you can identify
them all by sight,

10:23.884 --> 10:25.885
they're a lot easier
to avoid.

10:32.326 --> 10:35.068
And if you're not too
swamped with catching up,

10:35.111 --> 10:36.852
you should come by
the Bronze tonight.

10:36.897 --> 10:38.638
The who?The Bronze.

10:38.681 --> 10:40.856
It's the only club worth
going to around here.

10:40.900 --> 10:43.337
They let anybody in,
but it's still the scene.

10:43.380 --> 10:44.644
It's in the bad part
of town.

10:44.687 --> 10:46.210
Where's that?

10:46.254 --> 10:48.081
About a half a block
from the good part of town.

10:48.125 --> 10:49.649
We don't have
a whole lot of town here.

10:49.692 --> 10:50.911
But, um, you should show.

10:50.953 --> 10:52.346
Well, I'll try.

10:52.389 --> 10:54.043
[bell rings]Uh, thanks.

10:54.087 --> 10:56.133
Good. So, um,
I'll see you at gym,

10:56.177 --> 10:57.874
and you can tell me
absolutely everything

10:57.918 --> 10:59.354
there is to know about you.

10:59.397 --> 11:00.528
Great.

11:00.572 --> 11:02.836
Oh, that sounds like fun.

11:10.495 --> 11:12.496
Hello?

11:18.503 --> 11:21.681
Is anybody here?

11:28.991 --> 11:30.471
Ooh!

11:30.514 --> 11:32.561
Oh. Anybody's here.

11:32.604 --> 11:33.735
Can I help you?

11:33.779 --> 11:36.086
I was looking
for some...

11:36.129 --> 11:37.434
well, books.

11:37.479 --> 11:38.784
I'm new.

11:38.827 --> 11:40.437
Miss Summers?

11:41.438 --> 11:42.745
Good call.

11:42.788 --> 11:44.878
Guess I'm the only
new kid, huh?

11:44.921 --> 11:46.488
I'm Mr. Giles.

11:46.530 --> 11:48.010
The librarian.

11:48.054 --> 11:50.360
I was told
you were coming.

11:50.971 --> 11:52.841
Great.

11:52.885 --> 11:54.104
So, um, I'm gonna need

11:54.148 --> 11:55.539
Perspectives on 20th Century...

11:55.584 --> 11:57.238
I know what
you're after.

12:01.633 --> 12:04.985
That's not what
I'm looking for.

12:05.028 --> 12:06.508
Are you sure?

12:06.551 --> 12:08.770
I'm way sure.

12:09.510 --> 12:11.600
My mistake.

12:14.298 --> 12:16.169
So, what is it you sa...

12:21.000 --> 12:22.437
The new kid?

12:22.480 --> 12:24.004
She seems kind of weird to me.

12:24.047 --> 12:25.440
What kind of name
is Buffy?

12:25.482 --> 12:26.397
Hey, Aphrodesia.

12:26.441 --> 12:28.008
Oh, hey.

12:28.051 --> 12:30.313
Well, the chatter in the caf
is that she got kicked out

12:30.357 --> 12:31.402
and that's why her mom
had to get a new job.

12:31.446 --> 12:32.533
Neg!

12:32.576 --> 12:34.754
Pos! She was
starting fights.

12:34.797 --> 12:35.928
Negly!

12:35.971 --> 12:38.845
Well, I heard from Blue,
and she said...

12:38.888 --> 12:40.889
[screaming]

12:55.817 --> 12:57.907
Uh, hi.

12:57.951 --> 12:58.865
Willow, right?

12:58.908 --> 12:59.908
Why?

12:59.952 --> 13:00.996
I-I mean, hi.

13:01.041 --> 13:02.956
Uh, did you want me
to move?

13:02.999 --> 13:04.957
Why don't we start
with "Hi, I'm Buffy,"

13:05.000 --> 13:06.567
and then let's segue

13:06.610 --> 13:09.135
directly into me
asking you for a favor.

13:09.178 --> 13:10.528
It doesn't
involve moving,

13:10.572 --> 13:12.486
but it does involve hanging
out with me for a while.

13:12.529 --> 13:15.097
But aren't you hanging
out with Cordelia?

13:15.142 --> 13:16.273
I can't do both?

13:16.317 --> 13:18.187
Not legally.

13:18.231 --> 13:20.234
Look, I really want
to get by here.

13:20.277 --> 13:21.495
New school.

13:21.538 --> 13:23.889
And Cordelia's
been really nice...

13:23.932 --> 13:25.543
to me, anyway...

13:25.586 --> 13:27.457
but, um, I kind of have
this burning desire

13:27.501 --> 13:29.068
not to flunk
all my classes,

13:29.111 --> 13:30.940
and I heard a rumor that you
were the person to talk to

13:30.984 --> 13:32.375
if I wanted
to get caught up.

13:32.419 --> 13:33.942
Oh, I could totally
help you out.

13:33.986 --> 13:35.466
If you have
sixth period free,

13:35.509 --> 13:37.424
we could meet
in the library.

13:37.467 --> 13:39.209
Or not.

13:39.253 --> 13:41.081
Uh, we can meet
someplace quieter.

13:41.124 --> 13:43.735
Louder. Uh, that place just
kind of gives me the wiggins.

13:43.778 --> 13:46.042
Oh, it has that effect
on most kids.

13:46.086 --> 13:48.000
I love it, though.
It's a great collection,

13:48.043 --> 13:49.959
and the new librarian
is really cool.

13:50.003 --> 13:50.873
He's new?

13:50.917 --> 13:52.440
Yeah, he just started.

13:52.482 --> 13:54.485
He was a curator
at some British museum--

13:54.528 --> 13:56.573
or theBritish Museum.

13:56.618 --> 13:58.140
I'm not sure,
but he knows everything,

13:58.184 --> 13:59.447
and he brought all these
historical volumes

13:59.490 --> 14:00.927
and biographies,

14:00.970 --> 14:03.277
and am I the single
dullest person alive?

14:03.320 --> 14:04.495
Not at all.

14:04.538 --> 14:05.975
Hey, you guys busy?
Are we interrupting?

14:06.019 --> 14:07.716
We're interrupting.Hey.

14:07.759 --> 14:09.500
Hey.
Hey there.

14:09.543 --> 14:10.761
Buffy, this is Jesse
and that's Xander.

14:10.806 --> 14:12.807
XANDER: Oh, me and Buffy
go way back.

14:12.851 --> 14:14.678
Old friends, very close.

14:14.722 --> 14:16.202
Then there was that period
of estrangement,

14:16.245 --> 14:18.813
where I think we were
both growing as people,

14:18.857 --> 14:20.642
but now here we are,
like old times.

14:20.684 --> 14:21.686
I'm quite moved.

14:23.427 --> 14:24.688
Is it me,

14:24.732 --> 14:26.735
or are you turning
into a bibbling idiot?

14:26.778 --> 14:28.562
No, it's, uh, it's not you.

14:29.912 --> 14:32.436
Well, it's nice to meet
you guys, I think.

14:32.480 --> 14:34.047
Well, you know,
we wanted to welcome you,

14:34.090 --> 14:35.831
make you feel
at home--

14:35.875 --> 14:37.572
unless you have
a scary home.

14:37.615 --> 14:38.921
And to return this.

14:38.965 --> 14:40.662
The only thing
I can think

14:40.705 --> 14:42.663
is that you're building
a really little fence.

14:42.706 --> 14:44.491
Aha. No, um...

14:44.534 --> 14:46.450
a-actually,
it was for self-defense.

14:46.494 --> 14:48.278
Everyone has them in L.A.

14:48.322 --> 14:50.366
Pepper spray is just so passé.

14:50.411 --> 14:51.977
So what do you do for fun?
What do you like?

14:52.020 --> 14:54.110
What do you look for in
a man? Let's hear it.

14:54.153 --> 14:55.328
If you have any dark,

14:55.371 --> 14:57.070
painful secrets
you'd like us to publish?

14:57.113 --> 14:59.942
Gee, everyone wants
to know about me.

14:59.985 --> 15:00.942
How keen.

15:00.986 --> 15:02.162
Well, not much goes on

15:02.205 --> 15:04.380
in a one-Starbucks town
like Sunnydale.

15:04.424 --> 15:05.381
You're pretty big news.

15:05.426 --> 15:07.775
I'm not. Really.

15:07.818 --> 15:09.429
Are these guys
bothering you?

15:09.472 --> 15:11.258
Uh, no.

15:11.301 --> 15:13.346
She's not hanging out with us.

15:13.389 --> 15:14.347
Hey, Cordelia.

15:14.390 --> 15:15.957
Oh, please.

15:16.001 --> 15:17.437
I don't mean to interrupt
your downward mobility,

15:17.480 --> 15:18.961
but I just wanted to tell you

15:19.004 --> 15:20.962
that you won't be meeting
Coach Foster--

15:21.006 --> 15:22.399
the woman with the chest hair--

15:22.442 --> 15:23.966
because gym was canceled

15:24.009 --> 15:26.316
due to the extreme dead guy
in the locker.

15:26.360 --> 15:27.621
What?

15:27.664 --> 15:28.797
What are you
talking about?

15:28.840 --> 15:31.017
Some guy was stuffed
in Aura's locker.

15:31.059 --> 15:32.018
Dead?

15:32.061 --> 15:33.453
Totally dead.
Way dead.

15:33.496 --> 15:34.759
So, not just a little dead,
then?

15:34.802 --> 15:36.196
Don't you have
an elsewhere to be?

15:36.239 --> 15:38.153
You know, if you need
a shoulder to cry on

15:38.197 --> 15:39.938
or just to nibble on...

15:39.981 --> 15:41.244
How did he die?

15:41.288 --> 15:42.767
I don't know.

15:42.811 --> 15:43.812
Well, were there any marks?

15:43.855 --> 15:44.899
Morbid much?

15:44.943 --> 15:46.770
I didn't ask.

15:49.383 --> 15:53.299
Um, I got to book.
I'll-I'll see you guys later.

15:55.084 --> 15:57.607
What's her deal?

16:22.371 --> 16:24.984
Oh, great.

16:26.855 --> 16:28.856
Okay, what's the sitch?

16:28.899 --> 16:30.466
GILES:
Sorry?

16:30.510 --> 16:31.947
You heard about
the dead guy, right?

16:31.990 --> 16:33.687
The dead guy in the locker?

16:33.730 --> 16:34.994
Yes.

16:35.037 --> 16:37.038
'Cause it's the weirdest thing.

16:37.082 --> 16:39.999
He's got two little-little
holes in his neck

16:40.042 --> 16:41.956
and all his blood's
been drained.

16:42.000 --> 16:43.350
Isn't that bizarre?

16:43.393 --> 16:45.351
Aren't you just going,
"Ooh"?

16:45.394 --> 16:47.615
I was afraid of this.

16:47.658 --> 16:49.008
Well, I wasn't.

16:49.051 --> 16:51.096
It's my first day.

16:51.139 --> 16:54.013
I was afraid that I was gonna
be behind in all my classes,

16:54.056 --> 16:56.014
that I wouldn't make
any friends,

16:56.057 --> 16:58.451
that I would have
last month's hair.

16:58.495 --> 17:00.932
I didn't think there'd
be vampires on campus.

17:00.975 --> 17:02.107
And I don't care.

17:02.150 --> 17:03.717
Then why are you here?

17:04.980 --> 17:06.938
To tell you that...

17:06.981 --> 17:08.416
I don't care,

17:08.461 --> 17:09.941
which I don't,

17:09.983 --> 17:11.900
and have now told you,

17:11.942 --> 17:13.249
so...

17:13.291 --> 17:14.510
bye.

17:14.555 --> 17:16.991
Is he-- will he rise again?

17:17.036 --> 17:18.732
Who?

17:18.776 --> 17:19.777
The boy.

17:19.819 --> 17:20.865
No.

17:20.909 --> 17:22.692
He's just dead.

17:22.737 --> 17:24.652
Can you be sure?

17:24.694 --> 17:26.653
To make you a vampire,
they have to suck your blood,

17:26.695 --> 17:28.221
and then you have
to suck their blood.

17:28.262 --> 17:29.700
It's, like, a whole big
sucking thing.

17:29.743 --> 17:31.920
Mostly they're
just gonna kill you.

17:31.962 --> 17:33.964
Why am I still talking to you?

17:34.009 --> 17:36.010
You really have no idea
what's going on, do you?

17:36.055 --> 17:37.969
You think it's coincidence,
your being here?

17:38.012 --> 17:39.275
That boy was just the beginning.

17:39.318 --> 17:42.147
Why can't you people
just leave me alone?

17:42.191 --> 17:44.063
Because you are the slayer.

17:44.105 --> 17:45.977
To each generation
a slayer is born.

17:46.020 --> 17:47.892
One girl in all the world,

17:47.935 --> 17:48.980
a chosen one,

17:49.023 --> 17:50.590
one born with the strength...

17:50.634 --> 17:52.375
Strength and skill
to hunt the vampires,

17:52.419 --> 17:53.942
to stop the spread of
their evil blah, blah, blah.

17:53.984 --> 17:55.900
I've heard it, okay?

17:55.943 --> 17:57.815
I really don't understand
this attitude.

17:57.858 --> 17:59.164
You've accepted
your duty.

17:59.208 --> 18:00.775
You've slain vampires
before?

18:00.817 --> 18:02.384
Yeah, and I've both
been there and done that,

18:02.429 --> 18:03.517
and I'm moving on.

18:05.039 --> 18:08.086
What do you know
about this town?

18:08.130 --> 18:10.523
It's two hours on the freeway
from Neiman-Marcus.

18:10.567 --> 18:12.481
Dig a bit in the history
of this place,

18:12.526 --> 18:13.701
and you'll find
a-a steady stream

18:13.743 --> 18:15.049
of fairly odd
occurrences.

18:15.094 --> 18:16.311
I believe
this whole area

18:16.355 --> 18:17.835
is a center
of mystical energy,

18:17.878 --> 18:19.315
that things gravitate
towards it

18:19.358 --> 18:20.969
that-that you might
not find elsewhere.

18:21.011 --> 18:22.449
Like vampires.

18:22.491 --> 18:26.409
Like zombies, werewolves,
incubi, succubi--

18:26.452 --> 18:28.237
everything you've ever
dreaded was under your bed

18:28.280 --> 18:30.760
but told yourself couldn't
be by the light of day.

18:30.805 --> 18:32.894
They're all real.

18:32.936 --> 18:35.243
What, you, like, sent away
for the Time/Life series?

18:35.288 --> 18:37.333
Oh, w-well, yes.

18:37.376 --> 18:38.987
Did you get
the free phone?

18:39.029 --> 18:40.075
Um, the calendar.

18:40.118 --> 18:41.336
Cool.

18:41.381 --> 18:42.685
Wait. Okay.

18:42.730 --> 18:44.644
First of all,
I'm a vampire slayer.

18:44.688 --> 18:46.994
And secondly, I'm retired.

18:47.038 --> 18:49.171
Hey, I know.
Why don't you kill them?

18:49.214 --> 18:50.477
I'm a watcher.

18:50.519 --> 18:52.131
I-I haven't the skill.Oh, come on.

18:52.173 --> 18:53.958
Stake through the heart,
a little sunlight--

18:54.001 --> 18:55.742
it's like falling
off a log.

18:55.786 --> 18:58.528
A slayer slays,
a watcher...
Watches?

18:58.572 --> 18:59.789
Yes... no.

18:59.834 --> 19:04.055
He... he trains her.
He-he-he prepares her.

19:04.098 --> 19:05.448
Prepares me for what?

19:05.491 --> 19:07.450
For getting kicked out
of school?

19:07.493 --> 19:09.583
For losing all of my friends?

19:09.625 --> 19:12.628
For having to spend all of
my time fighting for my life

19:12.673 --> 19:15.371
and never getting to tell anyone
because I might endanger them?

19:15.414 --> 19:16.807
Go ahead.

19:16.851 --> 19:19.419
Prepare me.

19:26.773 --> 19:27.904
Damn.

19:34.346 --> 19:36.305
What?

19:36.348 --> 19:37.914
It's getting worse.

19:37.959 --> 19:39.742
What's getting worse?

19:40.961 --> 19:42.442
The influx
of the undead,

19:42.484 --> 19:43.964
the supernatural
occurrences.

19:44.008 --> 19:45.444
It's been building
for years.

19:45.488 --> 19:46.923
There's a reason
why you're here

19:46.968 --> 19:48.490
and a reason
why it's now.

19:48.535 --> 19:51.015
Because now is the time
my mom moved here.

19:51.058 --> 19:52.973
Something's coming.
Something-- something--

19:53.017 --> 19:54.845
something is--
is gonna happen here.

19:54.888 --> 19:55.977
Soon.

19:56.019 --> 19:58.458
Gee, can you vague
that up for me?

19:58.500 --> 20:00.547
The signs,
as far as I can tell,

20:00.589 --> 20:02.896
point to a crucial mystical
upheaval very soon.

20:02.940 --> 20:04.246
Days. Possibly less.

20:04.289 --> 20:05.377
Oh, come on.

20:05.421 --> 20:07.554
This is Sunnydale.

20:07.596 --> 20:09.817
How bad an evil
can there be here?

20:10.861 --> 20:12.863
[indistinct chatter]

20:40.978 --> 20:44.242
MAN:
The sleeper will wake.

20:47.507 --> 20:50.509
MAN:
The sleeper will wake.

20:55.340 --> 20:58.299
The sleeper will wake.

21:02.521 --> 21:04.740
The sleeper will wake,

21:04.785 --> 21:08.309
and the world will bleed.

21:12.444 --> 21:14.924
Amen!

21:22.324 --> 21:25.240
Hi, I'm an enormous slut.

21:25.284 --> 21:28.242
Hello, would you like
a copy of The Watchtower?

21:29.635 --> 21:31.550
I used to be so good at this.

21:31.594 --> 21:33.029
MOM:
Hi, hon.

21:33.074 --> 21:34.815
Hey.

21:34.857 --> 21:36.163
Are you going out tonight?

21:36.207 --> 21:37.512
Yeah, I'm going to a club.

21:37.557 --> 21:38.471
Oh.

21:38.513 --> 21:39.689
Will there be boys there?

21:39.732 --> 21:42.170
No, Mom, it's a nun club.

21:42.212 --> 21:44.259
Well, just be careful.

21:44.302 --> 21:45.433
I will.

21:48.088 --> 21:50.743
You know, I think we
can make it work here.

21:50.787 --> 21:53.355
I've got my positive
energy flowing.

21:53.398 --> 21:55.662
I'm gonna get the
gallery on its feet.

21:55.704 --> 21:58.055
Oh, uh, we may have
found a space today.

21:58.098 --> 22:00.230
That's great.

22:00.275 --> 22:03.017
Oh, and that school is a-a
very nurturing environment,

22:03.059 --> 22:04.278
which is just
what you need.

22:04.323 --> 22:05.498
Well, actually...

22:05.540 --> 22:06.499
Oh, not too nurturing.

22:06.541 --> 22:08.239
I know. You're 16.

22:08.282 --> 22:10.459
I've read all about the
dangers of overnurturing.

22:13.243 --> 22:14.810
It's hard.

22:14.855 --> 22:16.856
New town and everything.

22:16.900 --> 22:18.728
It is for me, too.

22:19.946 --> 22:21.904
I'm trying
to make it work.

22:21.949 --> 22:25.169
I'm going
to make it work.

22:25.212 --> 22:26.779
I know.

22:26.823 --> 22:28.825
Oh, you're a good
girl, Buffy.

22:28.868 --> 22:30.784
You just fell in
with the wrong crowd.

22:30.826 --> 22:32.828
But that is all
behind us now.

22:32.873 --> 22:33.874
It is.

22:33.916 --> 22:35.528
From now on,

22:35.570 --> 22:37.616
I'm only going to hang out
with the living--

22:37.660 --> 22:39.182
I mean, lively...

22:39.227 --> 22:40.183
people.

22:40.228 --> 22:41.708
Okay.

22:41.750 --> 22:43.099
You have fun.

22:54.547 --> 22:57.549
♪

23:26.709 --> 23:27.884
[cat yowls]

23:27.928 --> 23:29.494
[clattering]

23:34.281 --> 23:36.284
[siren wailing in distance]

24:05.182 --> 24:07.228
[grunts]

24:09.272 --> 24:10.710
[chuckles]

24:10.752 --> 24:12.580
Is there a problem, ma'am?

24:12.625 --> 24:15.236
Yeah, there's a problem.
Why are you following me?

24:15.278 --> 24:16.977
I know what you're thinking,

24:17.019 --> 24:18.934
but don't worry.

24:18.979 --> 24:20.980
I don't bite.

24:30.730 --> 24:32.818
The truth is...

24:32.862 --> 24:34.298
I thought
you'd be taller,

24:34.342 --> 24:36.648
or bigger muscles
and all that.

24:36.692 --> 24:37.779
Oh.

24:37.824 --> 24:39.781
You're pretty spry,
though.

24:39.826 --> 24:41.261
What do you want?

24:41.305 --> 24:42.915
The same thing you do.

24:42.959 --> 24:44.221
Okay...

24:44.265 --> 24:45.919
what do I want?

24:47.268 --> 24:49.051
To kill 'em.

24:49.096 --> 24:50.880
To kill 'em all.

24:50.923 --> 24:51.968
Sorry. That's incorrect.

24:52.011 --> 24:53.796
But you do get
this lovely watch

24:53.839 --> 24:55.537
and a year's supply
of Turtle Wax.

24:55.580 --> 24:57.538
What I want
is to be left alone.

24:57.583 --> 25:00.367
Do you really think
that's an option anymore?

25:00.411 --> 25:02.761
You're standing
at the mouth of hell,

25:02.805 --> 25:04.763
and it's about to open.

25:07.854 --> 25:11.640
Don't turn your back
on this.

25:12.597 --> 25:14.556
You've got to be ready.

25:14.599 --> 25:15.949
What for?

25:15.991 --> 25:18.038
For the harvest.

25:20.213 --> 25:21.954
Who are you?

25:21.998 --> 25:23.782
Let's just say...

25:23.826 --> 25:25.523
I'm a friend.

25:28.048 --> 25:31.268
Yeah, well, maybe I
don't want a friend.

25:31.311 --> 25:34.402
I didn't say I was yours.

25:50.287 --> 25:55.378
♪ Everybody wants to believe
in something ♪

25:55.423 --> 26:00.428
♪ Something that
fills them up inside ♪

26:00.471 --> 26:04.213
♪ Oh, everybody wants
the answers to questions ♪

26:04.258 --> 26:09.262
♪ To all the questions
