28:47.595 --> 28:49.249
♪ I got a lack of belief...

28:49.291 --> 28:52.077
So, you like to party
with the students?

28:52.121 --> 28:53.165
Isn't that kind of skanky?

28:53.209 --> 28:54.166
Uh, right.

28:54.210 --> 28:55.820
This is me having fun.

28:55.864 --> 28:57.344
Watching clown hair
prance about

28:57.386 --> 28:59.346
is hardly
my idea of a party.

28:59.388 --> 29:00.564
I'd much rather be
at home

29:00.607 --> 29:02.392
with a cup of Bovril
and a good book.

29:02.435 --> 29:04.654
You need
a personality, stat!

29:04.699 --> 29:05.655
This is a perfect
breeding ground

29:05.700 --> 29:06.788
for vampire activity.

29:06.832 --> 29:08.528
It's dark,
it's crowded...

29:08.571 --> 29:10.487
Besides, I knew you
were likely to show up,

29:10.530 --> 29:12.663
and I have to
make you understand.

29:12.707 --> 29:14.056
That the harvest
is coming, I know.

29:14.099 --> 29:15.057
Your friend told me.

29:15.101 --> 29:16.318
What did you say?

29:16.363 --> 29:18.104
The harvest. That mean
something to you?

29:18.146 --> 29:19.713
'Cause I'm
drawing a blank.

29:19.758 --> 29:21.454
I'm not sure.

29:21.498 --> 29:23.761
Who-- who
told you this?

29:23.805 --> 29:25.807
This guy--

29:25.851 --> 29:28.722
dark, gorgeous in
an annoying sort of way.

29:28.767 --> 29:30.333
I figured
you two were buds.

29:30.376 --> 29:32.465
No.

29:32.509 --> 29:36.035
The harvest. Did he
say anything else?

29:36.077 --> 29:38.298
Something about
the mouth of hell.

29:38.340 --> 29:40.430
I really
didn't like him.

29:40.473 --> 29:42.432
[song ends,
crowd cheers and applauds]

29:42.476 --> 29:44.478
MAN:
Sprung Monkey!

29:50.570 --> 29:52.921
Look at them,
throwing themselves about,

29:52.964 --> 29:56.184
completely unaware of the
danger that surrounds them.

29:56.229 --> 29:57.447
Lucky them.

29:57.490 --> 29:58.971
Or perhaps
you're right.

29:59.013 --> 30:00.711
Perhaps there is
no trouble coming.

30:00.755 --> 30:02.409
The signs could be wrong.

30:02.451 --> 30:05.064
It's not as though you've
been having the nightmares.

30:11.287 --> 30:13.071
My mom doesn't even
get out of bed anymore,

30:13.115 --> 30:15.074
and the doctor
says it's Epstein-Barr.

30:15.116 --> 30:17.597
I'm like, "Please,
it's chronic hepatitis,

30:17.641 --> 30:19.861
or at least chronic
fatigue syndrome."

30:19.904 --> 30:22.777
I mean, nobody cool has
Epstein-Barr anymore.

30:22.820 --> 30:24.344
Hey, Cordelia.

30:24.386 --> 30:26.301
Oh, yay, it's my stalker.

30:28.042 --> 30:29.958
Hey, you--
you look great.

30:30.001 --> 30:32.177
Well, I'm glad we
had this little chat.

30:32.221 --> 30:35.484
Listen, uh, you know,
you want to dance, you know?

30:35.528 --> 30:36.660
With you?

30:36.703 --> 30:37.791
Well, uh, yeah.

30:37.836 --> 30:39.271
Well, uh, no.

30:39.315 --> 30:40.969
Come on, guys.

30:44.798 --> 30:46.539
Fine.

30:46.583 --> 30:49.020
Plenty other fish in the sea.

30:49.064 --> 30:52.285
Oh, yeah, I'm on the prowl.

30:52.327 --> 30:54.634
Witness me prowling.

30:58.029 --> 31:01.423
I didn't say I'd never
slay another vampire.

31:01.468 --> 31:04.863
It's not like I have all these
fluffy bunny feelings for them.

31:04.905 --> 31:07.212
I'm just not going to get
way extracurricular with it.

31:07.256 --> 31:09.084
You know, if I
see one, sure...

31:09.127 --> 31:10.564
Will you be ready?

31:10.606 --> 31:12.000
There's so much you
don't know about them,

31:12.044 --> 31:13.959
about your own powers.

31:14.001 --> 31:15.916
A vampire appears
to a completely normal,

31:15.961 --> 31:17.396
until the feed is upon them.

31:17.440 --> 31:20.313
Only then do they reveal
their true demonic visage.

31:20.355 --> 31:22.141
You're like a textbook
with arms. I know this.

31:22.183 --> 31:23.619
The point is,

31:23.663 --> 31:26.492
a slayer should be able
to see them anyway,

31:26.536 --> 31:29.625
without looking,
without thinking.

31:29.670 --> 31:31.150
Well, can you tell me if there's

31:31.192 --> 31:33.413
a vampire
in this building?

31:33.455 --> 31:35.022
Maybe.You should know.

31:35.067 --> 31:38.505
Even through
this mass and this din,

31:38.548 --> 31:40.986
you should be
able to sense them.

31:41.028 --> 31:42.943
Well, try.

31:42.988 --> 31:44.250
Reach out
with your mind.

31:44.292 --> 31:45.816
You have to
hone your senses,

31:45.859 --> 31:47.817
focus until the energy
washes over you,

31:47.862 --> 31:49.384
till you-- you feel
every particle of...

31:49.429 --> 31:50.951
There's one.

31:50.996 --> 31:52.345
Where?

31:52.387 --> 31:54.913
Right there,
talking to that girl.

31:54.955 --> 31:56.131
You don't know...

31:56.174 --> 31:57.827
Oh, please!

31:57.872 --> 31:59.917
Look at his jacket. He's
got the sleeves rolled up.

31:59.961 --> 32:02.223
And the shirt?
Deal with that outfit

32:02.268 --> 32:03.616
for a moment.

32:03.660 --> 32:04.574
It's dated?

32:04.617 --> 32:06.315
It's carbon dated.

32:06.358 --> 32:08.490
Trust me, only someone living
underground for ten years

32:08.535 --> 32:09.928
would think that
was still the look.

32:09.971 --> 32:12.365
But you didn't...hone.

32:16.630 --> 32:17.935
Oh, no.

32:19.198 --> 32:20.199
Isn't that...?

32:20.241 --> 32:21.242
Willow.

32:21.287 --> 32:22.809
What's she doing?

32:22.853 --> 32:25.247
Seizing the moment.

32:25.290 --> 32:27.118
♪ We're formed in liquid

32:27.162 --> 32:28.816
♪ Pushed out still dripping

32:28.858 --> 32:32.819
♪ A world was thrown
before my eyes ♪

32:32.863 --> 32:35.561
♪ Now paint a picture

32:35.605 --> 32:38.086
♪ Crayon stick figures

32:38.130 --> 32:39.608
♪ With blue-haired people

32:39.653 --> 32:43.308
♪ Purple skies.

32:50.055 --> 32:53.013
♪

33:25.612 --> 33:26.481
[gasps]

33:26.526 --> 33:27.743
Aah!

33:27.788 --> 33:29.136
[gasps]

33:29.181 --> 33:30.660
Cordelia.

33:32.052 --> 33:35.056
God! What is your
childhood trauma?

33:35.099 --> 33:36.884
Have you guys
seen Willow?

33:36.926 --> 33:38.493
Did she
come by here?

33:38.538 --> 33:41.061
Why? Do you need to
attack her with a stick?

33:41.105 --> 33:43.717
Geez!

33:43.759 --> 33:45.935
Excuse me.

33:45.980 --> 33:49.983
I have to call everyone
I have ever met right now.

33:50.028 --> 33:53.291
♪ Pushed out still dripping,
a world was thrown... ♪

33:53.335 --> 33:55.076
That was quick.
Well done.

33:55.119 --> 33:56.947
I need to go to the library.
This harvest thing is...

33:56.990 --> 33:59.471
I didn't find them.

33:59.515 --> 34:01.909
The vampire is not dead?

34:01.951 --> 34:03.779
No, but my social life
is on the critical list.

34:03.824 --> 34:05.304
So what do we do?

34:05.346 --> 34:06.869
I'll take care of it.

34:06.913 --> 34:08.829
I-I need to
come with you, yes?

34:08.871 --> 34:11.918
Don't worry. One vampire
I can handle.

34:11.960 --> 34:14.878
So, um, what did you
say your name was?

34:16.880 --> 34:18.664
Darla.

34:18.708 --> 34:20.231
Darla. You know, I haven't
seen you around before.

34:20.275 --> 34:21.972
Are you from around here?

34:22.016 --> 34:25.150
No, but I
have family here.

34:25.193 --> 34:27.326
Have I met them?

34:27.369 --> 34:29.371
You probably will.

34:30.416 --> 34:33.418
♪

35:09.628 --> 35:11.108
Master.

35:17.550 --> 35:19.639
I am weak.

35:19.681 --> 35:23.032
Come the harvest,
you will be restored.

35:23.077 --> 35:25.079
The harvest.

35:25.123 --> 35:27.733
We're almost there.

35:27.777 --> 35:30.128
Soon you'll be free.

35:41.356 --> 35:43.315
I must be ready.

35:43.358 --> 35:45.186
I need my strength.

35:45.230 --> 35:47.666
I've sent your servants
to bring you some food.

35:47.710 --> 35:48.797
Good.

35:48.842 --> 35:49.798
Luke...

35:49.842 --> 35:50.887
Yes?

35:50.931 --> 35:53.585
Bring me
something... young.

35:55.414 --> 35:57.242
Sure is dark.

35:57.284 --> 35:58.807
It's night.

35:58.851 --> 36:00.983
Well, that's
a dark time, night.

36:01.027 --> 36:02.811
Traditionally.

36:02.856 --> 36:05.206
I still can't believe I've
never seen you at school.

36:05.250 --> 36:07.382
Do you have Mr. Chomsky
for history?

36:09.775 --> 36:11.690
Uh, the ice cream bar
is this way.

36:11.733 --> 36:13.867
It's past
Hamilton street.

36:13.909 --> 36:15.695
I know a shortcut.

36:26.052 --> 36:28.054
[laughter
and indistinct chatter]

36:29.273 --> 36:30.753
Hey, you leaving already?

36:30.797 --> 36:32.668
Oh, Xander,
have you seen Willow?

36:32.711 --> 36:34.016
Not tonight, no.

36:34.061 --> 36:36.106
She left with a guy.

36:36.150 --> 36:38.152
We're talking about
Willow, right?

36:38.195 --> 36:40.153
Scoring at the Bronze.
Working it, girl...

36:40.197 --> 36:42.635
No, I need to find her.
Where would he take her?

36:42.677 --> 36:45.637
Why? Oh, hey, I hope
he's not a vampire,

36:45.681 --> 36:49.250
because then you might
have to slay him.

36:49.293 --> 36:52.427
Was there
a school bulletin?

36:52.471 --> 36:54.603
Was it in
the newspaper?

36:54.646 --> 36:57.693
Is there anyone in this town
who doesn't know I'm the slayer?

36:57.737 --> 36:59.956
No, I only know that you
thinkthat you're the slayer,

37:00.000 --> 37:01.914
and the reason
why I know that...

37:01.958 --> 37:03.394
Well, whatever.
It doesn't matter.

37:03.438 --> 37:05.266
Just tell me,
where would Willow go?

37:05.309 --> 37:06.614
You're serious.

37:06.659 --> 37:08.313
We don't find her,

37:08.356 --> 37:11.315
and there's going to be one
more dead body in the morning.

37:11.358 --> 37:15.233
O-Okay, this is nice...
and scary.

37:15.275 --> 37:18.105
Are you sure
this is faster?

37:18.148 --> 37:21.150
Hey, you ever been
in one of these?

37:21.195 --> 37:23.327
No. Thank you.

37:25.199 --> 37:27.201
Come on.

37:30.726 --> 37:32.728
What are you afraid of?

37:35.514 --> 37:36.514
[whimpers]

37:37.342 --> 37:39.518
[grunting]

37:42.737 --> 37:45.045
That wasn't funny.

37:55.315 --> 37:58.318
Uh, I think
I'm going to go.

37:58.362 --> 37:59.625
Is that what you think?

38:05.673 --> 38:07.849
DARLA:
Is this the best you could do?

38:07.893 --> 38:09.677
She's fresh.

38:09.722 --> 38:12.246
Hardly enough to share.

38:12.289 --> 38:15.597
Why didn't you
bring your own?

38:15.641 --> 38:16.902
I did.

38:16.945 --> 38:18.164
Hey,

38:18.208 --> 38:19.208
wait up.

38:22.038 --> 38:23.300
Oh, my God, Jesse.

38:28.827 --> 38:31.438
You know, I think
you gave me a hickey.

38:32.744 --> 38:35.487
I got hungry
on the way.

38:35.530 --> 38:36.791
Jesse, let's
get out of here.

38:36.835 --> 38:38.925
Oh, you're
not going anywhere.

38:40.447 --> 38:42.275
Leave us alone.

38:42.320 --> 38:45.061
You're not
going anywhere

38:45.105 --> 38:46.541
until we've fed.

38:46.585 --> 38:48.108
Aah!

38:48.150 --> 38:51.153
Well, this is nice.

38:51.197 --> 38:55.289
It's a little bare,
but a dash of paint,

38:55.333 --> 38:57.900
a few throw pillows,
call it home.

38:57.943 --> 38:59.858
Who the hell are you?

38:59.902 --> 39:01.121
You mean there's actually
someone in this town

39:01.164 --> 39:03.123
who doesn't know already?

39:03.166 --> 39:05.038
Phew, that's a relief.
I'm telling you--

39:05.081 --> 39:07.518
having a secret identity in
this town is a job of work.

39:07.561 --> 39:08.737
Buffy, we bail now, right?

39:08.780 --> 39:10.434
Not yet.

39:10.478 --> 39:12.523
BUFFY: Okay, first of all,
what's with the outfit?

39:12.567 --> 39:16.266
Live in the now, okay?
You look like DeBarge.

39:18.443 --> 39:20.967
Now, we can do this
the hard way or...

39:21.010 --> 39:23.838
well, actually, there's
just the hard way.

39:23.882 --> 39:25.536
That's fine with me.

39:25.579 --> 39:27.713
Are you sure? Now, this is
not going to be pretty.

39:27.755 --> 39:30.932
We're talking violence,
strong language, adult content.

39:44.860 --> 39:47.210
See what happens
when you roughhouse?

39:47.253 --> 39:48.646
He was young and stupid.

39:48.690 --> 39:49.996
Xander, go.

39:50.039 --> 39:51.083
DARLA:
Don't go far.

39:51.126 --> 39:52.998
[grunting]

40:04.532 --> 40:07.447
You know, I just
wanted to start over,

40:07.492 --> 40:09.014
be like everybody else.

40:09.057 --> 40:10.972
Have some friends,
you know, maybe a dog.

40:11.016 --> 40:13.498
But, no.
You had to come here.

40:13.541 --> 40:15.413
You couldn't go suck
on some other town.

40:15.456 --> 40:16.501
Who are you?

40:16.543 --> 40:18.764
Don't you know?
[gasps]

40:20.592 --> 40:22.724
I don't care.

40:22.768 --> 40:23.768
[grunts]

40:26.902 --> 40:29.949
You were supposed to be bringing
an offering for the master.

40:29.992 --> 40:32.994
We're almost at harvest,
and you dally with this child?

40:33.039 --> 40:35.737
We had someone,
but then she came.

40:35.780 --> 40:37.260
She killed Thomas.

40:37.304 --> 40:40.045
Luke, she's strong.

40:40.088 --> 40:43.918
You go. I'll see if I can
handle the little girl.

40:54.800 --> 40:56.931
You're strong.

40:59.804 --> 41:03.373
I'm stronger.

41:03.416 --> 41:04.809
We'll get the police.

41:04.853 --> 41:06.637
It's just
a few blocks up.

41:06.681 --> 41:08.291
[growling]

41:12.077 --> 41:13.992
LUKE:
You're wasting my time.

41:14.036 --> 41:16.648
Hey, I had other
plans, too, okay?

41:26.005 --> 41:27.746
You think
you can stop me?

41:27.789 --> 41:29.268
Stop us?

41:29.311 --> 41:31.967
[gasping]

41:33.228 --> 41:36.797
You have no idea what
you're dealing with.

41:36.842 --> 41:37.972
Aah!

41:41.760 --> 41:44.371
And like a plague of boils,

41:44.414 --> 41:47.983
the race of man
covered the earth.

41:48.027 --> 41:50.856
But on the third day
of the newest light

41:50.898 --> 41:52.465
will come the harvest,

41:52.510 --> 41:57.036
when the blood of men
will flow as wine,

41:57.079 --> 42:01.083
when the master will walk
among them once more.

42:02.083 --> 42:03.432
The earth...

42:03.476 --> 42:06.523
will belong to the old ones.

42:08.438 --> 42:13.094
And hell itself
will come to town.

42:13.139 --> 42:15.402
[growls]

42:15.445 --> 42:17.230
[screaming]

42:20.233 --> 42:21.539
[panting]

42:37.641 --> 42:39.382
Aah!

42:39.425 --> 42:40.121
Aah!

42:40.166 --> 42:42.168
Amen.

43:25.733 --> 43:28.257
Grr. Argh.
